rComments: Habib is a great prof. He is super knowledgeable about modeling transportation demands. He is a great mathematician and super approachable. However, he is super generous and but shy

Great prof to teach probability theory. He is the one who make me 'Data Science' an interesting area to work in. Great mentor, highly knowledgeable, but super generous. You'll not guess who he is if you see him walking on campus, just like a student.

Great professor. His lectures were very clear and homework was challenging but workable. Workload is consistently heavy, especially during the last few weeks of class when we had a debate, EMME lab, and assignment all due at once. The final exam was very fair, and easy if you had done all the homework assignments independently, in my opinion.
